South Africa will deploy military medics to Gauteng to ease the burden on healthcare workers as new COVID-19 infections continue to rise. The province remains the epicentre of the outbreak, recording over 7 500 new cases in the last reporting period, while the country clocked over 11 700. During a briefing, along with experts on the progress made by Government, Acting Health Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane has also announced that vaccinations have now breached the 2-million mark. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">ï»¿</span>